    <note>Du(3) Nian [10665] See documentation for descendant, Zhen [10670]. I computed the generational lines of descent as follows: Zhen was grandnephew of Yan [1730] and great grandson of Wei [10666], who was grandson of Nian. Therefore Nian was the father of Yan's grandfather, Shuzhan [10674]. Since Yan was a 9th generation descendant of Tang Du You [3927], Nian was You's 5th generation descendant or great great grandson. This would date Nian's active year in ca. 930, which is fits well with the ancestry of both branches of the lineage.</note>
